    "body": "## Summary\n\n- Add `InjectTcgen05Fence`, a conservative TIR pass for Blackwell (`SM100+`) kernels that use TCGEN05/TMEM operations.\n- On Blackwell, regular thread synchronization primitives do **not** automatically synchronize TMEM state across threads. This pass inserts `tcgen05.fence::before_thread_sync` / `tcgen05.fence::after_thread_sync` at conservative handoff boundaries.\n- The current implementation is intentionally narrow. It is a no-op on non-`SM100` targets and on functions without TCGEN05/TMEM usage.\n\n### Current insertion rules\n\nWhen the function targets `SM100+` and contains TCGEN05/TMEM operations, the pass currently handles three patterns:\n\n1. Wrap every `tvm_storage_sync(\"shared\")` / `tvm_storage_sync(\"shared.dyn\")` as:\n   ```cuda\n   tl::tcgen05_before_thread_sync();\n   __syncthreads();\n   tl::tcgen05_after_thread_sync();\n   ```\n2. Insert `tcgen05_after_thread_sync()` after `mbarrier_wait_parity(...)` when a forward linear scan reaches TCGEN05/TMEM use before another synchronization boundary.\n3. Insert `tcgen05_before_thread_sync()` before `ptx_arrive_barrier(...)` / `ptx_arrive_cluster_barrier(...)` when a backward linear scan reaches TCGEN05/TMEM use after the previous synchronization boundary.\n\n### Explicit non-goals / exclusions in this PR\n\n- This PR does **not** claim to infer arbitrary mbarrier protocols.\n- This PR does **not** add an extra `before_thread_sync` around `tcgen05_mma_arrive()`, because the underlying `tcgen05.commit.*.mbarrier` already provides the producer-side ordering.\n- The SM100 examples still keep manual fences where that makes the handoff points explicit.\n\n### Changes\n\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `src/transform/inject_tcgen05_fence.cc` | Conservative fence injection logic for shared syncs and simple linear wait/use, use/arrive patterns |\n| `tilelang/engine/phase.py` | Run the pass after `ThreadSync(\"shared\")` / `ThreadSync(\"shared.dyn\")` |\n| `tilelang/transform/__init__.py` | Python pass registration and docstring |\n| `src/target/codegen_cuda.cc` | Keep the checked CUDA codegen path for TCGEN05 fence intrinsics |\n| `src/op/builtin.h` | Remove duplicate TCGEN05 fence declarations |\n| `testing/python/transform/test_tilelang_transform_inject_tcgen05_fence.py` | Regression coverage for insertion scope and non-duplication |\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] `cmake -S . -B build`\n- [x] `cmake --build build -j 8`\n- [x] `python -m pytest -q testing/python/transform/test_tilelang_transform_inject_tcgen05_fence.py`\n- [x] `python -m pytest -q testing/python/transform/test_tilelang_transform_lower_shared_barrier.py`\n- [x] Verified generated CUDA source still emits `tl::tcgen05_before_thread_sync()` / `tl::tcgen05_after_thread_sync()` through `tilelang.lower(..., target=\"cuda\")`\n- [ ] End-to-end correctness/perf validation on Blackwell hardware\n\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **New Features**\n  * Automatic conservative TCGEN05 fence insertion for SM100+ targets and new TCGEN05 load/store intrinsics with end-to-end codegen support.\n\n* **Documentation**\n  * README updated to describe automatic fence insertion behavior, targeted patterns, and limitations.\n\n* **Tests**\n  * New tests validating fence injection, lowered TCGEN05 intrinsics, barrier-handling behavior, and target-specific no-ops.\n\n* **Bug Fixes / Examples**\n  * SM100 example kernels cleaned up to remove redundant manual TCGEN05 thread-sync calls.\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
